14. Longest Common Prefix

Write a function to find the longest common prefix string amongst an array of strings.

If there is no common prefix, return an empty string "".
Example 1:

Input: strs = ["flower","flow","flight"]
Output: "fl"

class Solution {
    public String longestCommonPrefix(String[] strs) {
        String res=strs[0];
        for(int i=1;i<strs.length;i++)
        {
            res=cm(res,strs[i] );
        }
        return res;
        
    }
    public static String cm(String s1,String s2)
    {
        StringBuilder sb=new StringBuilder();
        int n=Math.min(s1.length(),s2.length() );
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            if( s1.charAt(i)==s2.charAt(i) )
            {
                sb.append( s1.charAt(i));
            }
            else
            {
                break;
            }
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }
}

Time Complexity (TC)
n = number of strings (strs.length)
m = length of the shortest string

Outer Loop
for(int i=1;i<strs.length;i++)
Runs (n - 1) times → where n = number of strings

Function cm(s1, s2)
for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
Compares characters one by one
Runs up to min(length of s1, length of s2)
Total:

O(n * m)

💾 Space Complexity (SC)
Extra Space Used:
StringBuilder sb → stores prefix → O(m)
